publish.text96.message: Peer assessment of group work, including within-group and inter-group assessment:

publish.text97.message: - Peer assessment within the group, i.e. students evaluate the performance of other members of the same group in the assignment;

publish.text98.message: - Intergroup peer assessment, i.e. students evaluate the work of other groups

publish.text99.message: Timing and format of peer evaluation

publish.text100.message: - Student peer evaluation begins after the deadline for assignment submission. (Note: If you submit an insufficient number of assignments, the assignment will be converted to instructor grading)

publish.text101.message: - Teams that fail to submit assignments on time will not participate in inter-group peer assessment; Assignments submitted after the deadline for submission are graded by the instructor.

publish.text102.message: - Students participating in the peer evaluation must complete the evaluation task before the deadline of the peer assessment, otherwise a certain percentage of points will be deducted.

publish.text103.message: - Peer evaluations within and between groups are anonymous, i.e. the details of the evaluation are only visible to the teacher.

publish.text105.message: In peer evaluation, students are required to mark all other members of the group.

publish.text106.message: Inter-group mutual evaluation, evaluation tasks are not assigned across classes, and students can only evaluate the work of other groups in the class. The system randomly assigns students a specified number of assignments from the groups participating in the peer assessment.

publish.text108.message: Student peer evaluation score = average score of peer evaluation between groups * weight of peer evaluation between groups + average score of peer evaluation within group * weight of peer evaluation within - deduction of points for uncompleted peer evaluation tasks

publish.text109.message: - Points deduction for peer evaluation tasks: If a student does not complete the evaluation task, 2% of the total assignment score will be deducted for each missing person in the group peer evaluation, or for each missing group in the group peer evaluation. The cumulative deduction of points is capped at 20% until the deduction is exhausted.

publish.text110.message: - After the completion of the peer evaluation, the work that has not been evaluated must be graded by the teacher. Teachers can also regrade based on the student's peer scores. After the teacher re-grads, the final score of the individual student will be based on the teacher's rating.
